<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3867] Disablethrift and Enablethrift can leaves behind zombie connections on THSHA server</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3867</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While doing nodetool disable thrift we disable selecting threads and close them... but the connections are still active...&lt;br/&gt;
Enable thrift creates a new Selector threads because we create new ThriftServer() which will cause the old connections to be zombies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the right fix will be to call server.interrupt(); and then close the connections when they are done selecting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
